author: Ryan Tracy
title: What President Donald Trump Can—and Can’t—Do for Wall Street
text:
President Donald Trump’s planned executive actions on financial deregulation Friday give momentum to a cause Wall Street has been pursuing for years, sparking alarm from Democrats and consumer groups.
But the orders don’t change the fact that there are practical limitations to what the White House can do on its own to undo the Obama administration’s regulatory policies.
